FBIS3-57164 "drsov015_b_94044" FBIS-SOV-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Defense Ministry Debates Military Reform LD2201031694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0200 GMT 22 Jan 94 LD2201031694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Russian Defense Ministry has held an expanded interdepartmental conference to discuss a concept of military-legal reform for the Russian Armed Forces. It was noted during the conference that the purposes, goals, and stages of a military-legal reform should fit the concept for the structure of the country's armed forces and the principles of a democratic, law-based state. Therefore, they will be drawn up in accordance with the Constitution and the Russian military doctrine. It is planned to complete the drafting of a concept for military-legal reform in June 1994.
